      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "KAI MONDO (4) grows a leg for hoop Olzard who has two wins and two placings from just four steers and will be ready to peak now fourth run back from the break. Again gets the benefit of her 2kg claim and should be able to sit up on speed from the inside alley. Goes on top. I AM VOODOO (6) brings south-eastern QLD formlines to the table and should find this assignment a touch easier. Expect him to play a major role in the finish. The well-related COCHRANE (3) (half to 2xG2 winner Cifrado) has placed two of three over this track and trip and is usually about the money. In the mix. DOUBTING EYE (1) saves his best form for this course and distance and can improve sharply on recent efforts. Worth another chance. DEHORNED UNICORN (2) is a last-start winner who shouldn't be slept on.",
